    "body": "* Introduced the `AnnotateReadOnlyParams` transformation to annotate read-only handle parameters in PrimFuncs, enabling the generation of `const` qualifiers in CUDA codegen.\r\n* Updated `PrintFunctionSignature` and `AddFunction` methods to utilize the new attribute `tl.readonly_param_indices`, enhancing performance by allowing read-only cache loads.\r\n* Modified the optimization pipeline to include the new annotation step, improving the overall efficiency of the code generation process.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * GPU kernels can mark handle parameters as read-only so generated kernels emit const-qualified pointers; GPU templates updated for improved const-correctness across CUDA/HIP/TMA backends.\n  * New transformation pass to detect and annotate read-only parameters, integrated into the optimization pipeline and exposed in the public API.\n\n* **Chores**\n  * Bumped apache-tvm-ffi minimum version to >=0.1.3.\n  * Minor example cleanup.\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Added test validating read-only parameter annotation and const-qualified GPU kernel signatures.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
